    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-05-05</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-05-13T20:51:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Prescription Drug Price Fairness Act - Amends part D (Voluntary Prescription Drug Benefit Program) of title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to: (1) grant the Secretary of Health and Human Services authority similar to that of the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to negotiate the lowest possible prices for outpatient prescription drugs; (2) include prices charged for covered outpatient drugs to certain Federal agencies in the determination of best price for such drugs under the Medicaid program; and (3) allow States, in entering into rebate agreements with manufacturers, to form pools to negotiate price concessions from the manufacturers for covered outpatient drugs.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Prescription Drug Price Fairness Act</title>
